title: Assuring the Security of the State of Qatar

enrichment.summary: This executive order commits the United States to defending the State of Qatar against any armed attack, viewing such aggression as a threat to U.S. security. It directs relevant officials to maintain coordinated planning and to take necessary diplomatic, economic, or military actions to protect Qatar and promote peace and stability in the region.
potential_concerns: The commitment to defend Qatar militarily may increase deployment frequency and combat risks for military-personnel-active-duty, affecting their safety and family stability.
The order could escalate tensions with rival Middle East states, potentially straining U.S. diplomatic relations and increasing risks to foreign-government-officials in the region.

Enhanced U.S. military involvement in Qatar might provoke retaliatory attacks on critical infrastructure, indirectly impacting citizens-of-specific-countries-by-eo-designation including civilians in Qatar.
Extended diplomatic and military commitments could divert resources from other foreign policy priorities, affecting U.S. ability to respond to other global conflicts or crises.
